    "question_id" : 7325579,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>NoClassDefFoundError doesn't give much of a clue as to what went wrong inside the static block.  It is good practice to always have a block like this inside of static { ... } initialization code:</p>\n\n<pre><code>static {\n  try {\n\n    ... your init code here\n\n  } catch (Throwable t) {\n    LOG.error(\"Failure during static initialization\", t);\n    throw t;\n  }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3849657,
      "reputation" : 389,
      "user_id" : 3190140,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 38,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/PdAxz.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "KerenSi",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3190140/kerensi"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1512662987,
    "last_edit_date" : 1512662987,
    "creation_date" : 1405586284,
    "answer_id" : 24798674,
    "question_id" : 7325579,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I had the same exception, this is how I solved the problem:</p>\n\n<p><strong>Preconditions:</strong></p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><p>Junit class (and test), that extended another class.</p></li>\n<li><p>ApplicationContext initialized using spring, that init the project.</p></li>\n<li><p>The Application context was initialized in @Before method</p></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Init the application context from @BeforeClass method, since the parent class also required some classes that were initialized from within the application context.</p>\n\n<p>Hope this will help.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3332564,
      "reputation" : 339,
      "user_id" : 2801140,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/aebb8cb026bbaf6e7eaa3e196f00f51b?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "TriMix",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2801140/trimix"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1418845612,
    "creation_date" : 1418845612,
    "answer_id" : 27533620,
    "question_id" : 7325579,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>As mentioned above, this could be a number of things.  In my case I had a statically initialized variable which relied on a missing entry in my properties file.  Added the missing entry to the properties file and the problem was solved.  </p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 7165219,
        "reputation" : 45,
        "user_id" : 5474564,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/a10be2984d596543633ca51f93d07844?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
        "display_name" : "MonkeyKing",
